  "prompt": "How can we solve log base 3 of 28 without calculator?",
  "response": "To solve log base 3 of 28 without a calculator, we can use the change of base formula and logarithm properties. Here's a step-by-step approach:\n\n1) The change of base formula states that:\n   log\u2083(28) = ln(28) / ln(3)\n\n2) We'll need to estimate ln(28) and ln(3)\n\n3) Approximations:\n   ln(3) \u2248 1.10\n   ln(28) \u2248 3.33\n\n4) Divide:\n   log\u2083(28) \u2248 3.33 / 1.10\n             \u2248 3.03\n\n5) To verify, we can check:\n   3^3.03 \u2248 28\n\nSo, log\u2083(28) \u2248 3.03\n\nAnother method would be to use trial and error:\n\u2022 3\u00b2 = 9\n\u2022 3\u00b3 = 27\n\u2022 3\u2074 = 81\n\nThis suggests the answer is slightly over 3, which matches our calculation.\n\nThe approximate answer is 3.03.",
